🟧🤍🟩 Celebrating the 77th Republic Day of India — Honoring 150 Years of Vande Mataram 🟧🤍🟩      

26 January 2026 | Kartavya Path, New Delhi  

Today, India celebrates its 77th Republic Day, a moment of immense pride as we honor the historic day when the Constitution of India 
came into effect in 1950, transforming our nation into a sovereign, democratic republic. This year’s celebration carries a deeper 
cultural resonance with the theme:      

⭐ "150 Years of Vande Mataram"🟧🤍🟩      

A tribute to the timeless national song that inspired courage, unity, and an unbreakable spirit during our freedom struggle.
🌟 Highlights of the 2026 Republic Day Celebrations  

✨ International Dignitaries    
India hosts two distinguished chief guests:
Antonio Costa, President of the European Council
Ursula von der Leyen, President of the European Commission 🟦   
Their presence symbolizes India’s growing global partnerships and strategic engagement with Europe.

🎨 Cultural Grandeur at Kartavya Path
This year’s parade has been one of the most diverse and innovative:

🎬 First-Ever Indian Cinema Tableau
Designed by acclaimed filmmaker Sanjay Leela Bhansali, this tableau honors the cultural legacy and global impact of Indian cinema—its art,
music, storytelling, and inspiration.

🚩 30 Tableaux Showcasing India’s Diversity 🟦🤍🟦
States, Union Territories, and various ministries present their vision of
Aatmanirbhar Bharat (Self-Reliant India) through vibrant, artistic displays representing culture, innovation, and progress.

✨ Mass Cultural Performances
Over 2,500 artists from across the country perform at Kartavya Path, showcasing India’s unity in diversity through classical, folk, and contemporary art forms.

✈️ Spectacular Flypast by the Indian Air Force 🟦🤍🟦
A breathtaking highlight was the "Sindoor" formation, featuring: 🟥
Rafale
Su-30 MKI
MiG-29
Jaguar aircraft 🛩️
A powerful salute to India’s defense strength and technological advancement.

🟧🤍🟩 A Day of Pride, Progress & Purpose

Republic Day reminds us of our shared journey -
From colonial rule to constitutional liberty,
From struggle to self-reliance,
From dreams to global achievements.
As we honor 150 years of Vande Mataram, we celebrate the values that bind us:
Freedom, Unity, Courage, Innovation, and Nation-building.

Let’s continue contributing to India’s 🛩️ growth with dedication and integrity.  

Jai Hind! 🟧🤍🟩

